No PEM or DER certificate files are committed here.

TLS certificates for the contract smoke test (T9) are generated in-memory
at test time using the `rcgen` crate.  This avoids:

  - Secret-scanner false positives on committed private keys.
  - Cert expiry causing test failures over time.
  - Any dependency on openssl tooling in the CI environment.

The in-memory path is: rcgen::generate_simple_self_signed -> serialize to
PEM bytes -> feed into axum_server::tls_rustls::RustlsConfig::from_pem and
reqwest::Certificate::from_pem.  No disk I/O, no file rotation needed.
